This script is running on an LSF (Load Sharing Facility) batch system.  The script uses CMSSW (CMS Software) version 7.5.8_patch3 and sets the SCRAM architecture to slc6_amd64_gcc491.  It also uses the `eos` command for accessing files on the EOS (Enstore Object Storage) system. The script uses a proxy file specified by `$X509_USER_PROXY` for authentication.

The script takes an input file (`__INPUT__`) and runs an executable (`__EXECUTABLE__`) with various arguments. It then copies the output file to EOS and renames it to `basename __OUTPUT__`. 

The placeholders in the script (e.g., `__INPUT__`, `__EXECUTABLE__`, `__TAG__`) represent variables that are likely provided when submitting the script to the batch system.
